article.headline: Ark.-Pine Bluff 70, Alabama A&amp,M 56
article.story: PINE BLUFF, Ark. -- Savalance Townsend helped Arkansas-Pine Bluff come back to defeat Alabama A&M 70-56 Monday night. Townsend's nine-point effort allowed the Golden Lions (3-11) to take a 33-28 lead going into the second half. Tyree Glass led with 13 points, Townsend had 12 and Ricky Parks scored 11. Eric Brooks hit 10 and had five assists. Alabama A&M (3-9) had a 24-23 lead with 2:55 left in the first half on Jonathan Inman's two free throws. Casey Canty led the Bulldogs with 17 points and six rebounds.
